GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_TerminologyControl> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_TerminologyControl> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#TerminologyControl> ;
    narr:childCount "29"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub tracks the project's deliberate terminology control — what a term is called, who sees it, and when it changed. The dominant trajectory is a move toward plain English and away from metaphor: conviction levels were [renamed from stake/boulder/foundation to claim/decision/principle](narr:Narrative_ConvictionLevelRename) in Mar 2026 because [the metaphors needed decoding](narr:Obs_ConvictionLabelPlainEnglish), and the cognition model was [simplified to remember → process → perspective](narr:Narrative_CognitionModelSimplification), dropping Jungian 'individuate'/'internalize'. User-facing/internal splits are enforced: ['shifts' is what users see, 'optometrist model' is internal](narr:Claim_ShiftsTerminology) (Jul 2025), and ['lenses', 'story drafts', 'telltales' were redefined or retired](narr:Observation_VocabDefinitions). Separately, ['memory' was let go for 'installable expertise'](narr:StyleObs_InstallableExpertiseTerm) (Mar 2026), an outcome-framing move. Beneath these sit canonical brand terms — [lowercase 'aswritten'](narr:StyleObs_1), ['collective memory'](narr:StyleObs_CollectiveMemory), ['lens'/'micro-telltale'](narr:StyleObs_LensMicroTelltale), 'Priority Stack', 'Pilot', SEAL — plus a register of style markers (staccato fragments, scare-quotes, backtick code spans) and a stated rule to [preserve new vocabulary verbatim](narr:StyleObs_VerbatimVocabulary).""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ShiftsTerminology> ;
